 I will generally always write it as request or REQ, and so the user information, that is pretty much the same as what's in the template tag, well template context user, user is authenticated, their user name, their email, I could have had rec.user.id if I wanted here, and otherwise it's not logged in, and then I just throw this back as a simple HTTP response.

