 So one of them is checking to see if user is authenticated, so I have two views in here, one is I'm gonna protect it manually, and that's so you can see how it works, but it's really not the right way to do it.

00:05:56.000 --> 00:06:09.000
 I mean, you can do it this way, but it's like there's always a better way in Django, always a better way in Django. So here we have a class-based view, and we ask is the user authenticated?

00:06:09.000 --> 00:06:25.000
 If the user is authenticated, we just do whatever. Now there might be a whole bunch of stuff in here, there might be a whole bunch of stuff, but I'm just gonna render the thing so that that's a view, so I'm protecting this particular manual protect view, but if you're authenticated, you can see it, right?

